00:00:45,211 --> 00:00:48,131
MENTAL MASSAGE
CHOOSE AND ENTER

2
00:00:48,798 --> 00:00:50,842
EFFECTS OF MENTAL MASSAGE
INCREASED SELF-ESTEEM

3
00:01:17,118 --> 00:01:18,203
The green onion.

4
00:01:19,412 --> 00:01:20,371
It's good.

5
00:01:30,131 --> 00:01:31,132
Flop!

6
00:01:32,217 --> 00:01:35,345
The bag just flopped out of nowhere.
Flop! Did you see that?

7
00:01:35,428 --> 00:01:38,640
Oh, no. What do we do? This is bad.

8
00:01:47,857 --> 00:01:48,942
Aren't you going home?

9
00:01:50,485 --> 00:01:52,403
I'm trying to pull myself together
and read the script.

10
00:01:52,487 --> 00:01:53,738
It's been hours.

11
00:01:53,822 --> 00:01:55,990
I can do it for hours or for days
if I want to.

12
00:01:56,116 --> 00:01:58,076
I have no one to drink with.

13
00:01:58,159 --> 00:01:59,577
You've never had anyone to drink with.

14
00:02:01,246 --> 00:02:03,331
-I guess the script is good.
-That's why I'm doing this.

15
00:02:03,414 --> 00:02:04,499
I see.

16
00:02:04,874 --> 00:02:07,585
Then why did you tell me
not to work on it when I asked?

17
00:02:07,836 --> 00:02:09,087
Because you would ruin it.

18
00:02:10,380 --> 00:02:12,966
-You said it wasn't good.
-It's not good when it's done by you.

19
00:02:13,091 --> 00:02:14,968
I'm the only one
who can pull off this script.

20
00:02:15,385 --> 00:02:16,761
When will you stop looking down on me?

21
00:02:16,845 --> 00:02:18,972
I'll do it as long as you are alive
by my side.

22
00:02:20,265 --> 00:02:21,474
You're my true friend.

23
00:02:21,558 --> 00:02:23,143
That doesn't make me a true friend.

24
00:02:23,226 --> 00:02:24,686
Forget it. Let's go and have some beer.

25
00:02:24,769 --> 00:02:26,396
Forget it. You should go alone.

26
00:02:28,273 --> 00:02:29,691
That's enough. Let's just go.

27
00:02:29,774 --> 00:02:31,109
That's enough. Get out.

28
00:02:31,776 --> 00:02:35,029
You punk. Let's just go. Hurry.

29
00:02:44,831 --> 00:02:45,957
Why are you depressed again?

30
00:02:46,040 --> 00:02:47,709
Don't even ask.

31
00:02:48,293 --> 00:02:50,295
What is it? Is it because of So-yeong?

32
00:02:50,795 --> 00:02:53,381
My gosh. It's just a boy-girl problem.

33
00:02:53,464 --> 00:02:54,465
Don't ask.

34
00:02:55,925 --> 00:02:57,135
My gosh.

35
00:03:04,642 --> 00:03:07,520
In-guk, how did you tell her
your feelings?

36
00:03:07,812 --> 00:03:09,230
So-yeong told me her feelings first.

37
00:03:09,314 --> 00:03:11,107
Whatever. How did she do that?

38
00:03:11,232 --> 00:03:12,692
I'm not telling you.

39
00:03:17,989 --> 00:03:19,324
Is there anything you want to eat?

40
00:03:19,699 --> 00:03:21,534
I want a corn dog. Have it delivered.

41
00:03:21,618 --> 00:03:22,577
All right.

42
00:03:22,660 --> 00:03:24,954
Hey. You picked at your food earlier.

43
00:03:25,038 --> 00:03:26,873
But you want to eat a corn dog
when you're depressed?

44
00:03:26,956 --> 00:03:28,374
I want it because I'm depressed.

45
00:03:28,458 --> 00:03:31,377
He's right. You can eat it.
I'll buy it all.

46
00:03:31,586 --> 00:03:33,254
-Okay?
-My gosh.

47
00:03:34,714 --> 00:03:36,341
I guess it's here.

48
00:03:38,343 --> 00:03:40,303
-Hyo-bong is here.
-What?

49
00:03:40,386 --> 00:03:41,679
Your corn dog is here.

50
00:03:41,763 --> 00:03:44,974
-My gosh.
-It's here.

51
00:03:46,517 --> 00:03:48,019
It must be delicious.

52
00:03:50,772 --> 00:03:53,316
-My gosh.
-It looks amazing.

53
00:03:53,399 --> 00:03:55,610
-Let me see.
-This one?

54
00:03:55,693 --> 00:03:57,445
-I want the thin one.
-The thin one?

55
00:03:57,528 --> 00:03:59,781
-Goodness.
-Do you want some ketchup?

56
00:04:00,865 --> 00:04:02,617
Here. Do you like it?

57
00:04:02,825 --> 00:04:03,785
That's enough.

58
00:04:03,868 --> 00:04:06,496
Here? Okay.

59
00:04:06,579 --> 00:04:10,333
My gosh. It has a lot of cheese in it.

60
00:04:14,545 --> 00:04:15,505
There you go.

61
00:04:15,588 --> 00:04:17,757
All right. Tell me now.

62
00:04:17,840 --> 00:04:19,592
We talked on an instant messenger.

63
00:04:20,802 --> 00:04:21,970
An instant messenger?

64
00:04:22,053 --> 00:04:23,054
Yes.

65
00:04:24,222 --> 00:04:26,266
-Is that it?
-Then what?

66
00:04:26,557 --> 00:04:29,811
So you ask someone out
on an instant messenger?

67
00:04:29,894 --> 00:04:33,314
If you like it, you start dating.
And if you don't, it's just over?

68
00:04:33,856 --> 00:04:34,857
Then what?

69
00:04:35,733 --> 00:04:38,152
-Isn't there anything else?
-Like what?

70
00:04:40,405 --> 00:04:43,241
All right. Eat up, schoolkid.

71
00:04:47,745 --> 00:04:50,999
In-guk, I told you not to sigh like that.

72
00:04:52,083 --> 00:04:53,418
Kids can sigh too.

73
00:04:53,501 --> 00:04:54,836
Why would you say that?

74
00:04:54,919 --> 00:04:56,462
I know.

75
00:05:10,393 --> 00:05:12,895
You wanted to eat a corn dog with beer.
Why aren't you drinking?

76
00:05:12,979 --> 00:05:16,274
I have an important meeting tomorrow.

77
00:05:16,649 --> 00:05:19,152
I will go to persuade a rookie writer.

78
00:05:19,444 --> 00:05:20,862
I should look good.

79
00:05:20,945 --> 00:05:22,822
Why do you need to look good
to persuade a writer?

80
00:05:22,905 --> 00:05:25,616
If I think that I look pretty good,

81
00:05:25,700 --> 00:05:27,118
it makes me more confident.

82
00:05:33,166 --> 00:05:36,335
You want to look good
while eating a corn dog.

83
00:05:36,919 --> 00:05:38,379
I think you're confident enough.

84
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:43,801
You'll see tomorrow.

85
00:05:46,888 --> 00:05:48,556
What? Tomorrow?

86
00:05:52,351 --> 00:05:53,978
See you. I should get going.

87
00:05:54,062 --> 00:05:55,855
-Why are you going that way?
-What?

88
00:05:56,397 --> 00:05:58,232
-I'm working away from the office.
-What do you mean?

89
00:05:58,316 --> 00:06:00,193
I work outside today.
I should go this way.

90
00:06:00,276 --> 00:06:02,236
Then you should've just gone there.
Why did you come?

91
00:06:02,320 --> 00:06:04,405
You said you were walking me
to school on your way to work.

92
00:06:04,489 --> 00:06:07,158
Just stop nagging me and get in there.

93
00:06:07,784 --> 00:06:09,160
Don't fight with So-yeong.

94
00:06:09,243 --> 00:06:11,788
I never fought with her. She just hit me.

95
00:06:29,430 --> 00:06:31,474
Why are you all dressed up like that?

96
00:06:33,142 --> 00:06:35,353
You look better
when you're not dressed up.

97
00:06:41,818 --> 00:06:43,069
You're staring at the wall.

98
00:06:43,152 --> 00:06:44,695
Do you want to go out with me?

99
00:06:48,825 --> 00:06:50,118
Are you saying that to the wall?

100
00:06:50,201 --> 00:06:51,994
I really wanted to say this,

101
00:06:53,037 --> 00:06:54,914
but I just couldn't do it
looking into your eyes.

102
00:06:56,541 --> 00:06:57,542
Why not?

103
00:06:59,752 --> 00:07:02,672
This is crazy. What's wrong with me?

104
00:07:07,009 --> 00:07:08,928
Was it the first time I saw you?

105
00:07:09,512 --> 00:07:11,139
I guess it was around that time.

106
00:07:13,349 --> 00:07:15,768
-What do you mean?
-That's when I fell for you.

107
00:07:21,607 --> 00:07:23,651
Undoubtedly, my feelings...

108
00:07:27,321 --> 00:07:28,281
What?

109
00:07:30,116 --> 00:07:31,242
It's weird.

110
00:07:31,868 --> 00:07:32,994
It's so lame.

111
00:07:37,832 --> 00:07:40,209
What's so undoubted?

112
00:07:40,751 --> 00:07:42,086
"Will you go on a date with me?"

113
00:07:42,170 --> 00:07:43,629
"A date?"

114
00:07:43,838 --> 00:07:46,883
"Date." It sounds somewhat old-fashioned.

115
00:07:47,633 --> 00:07:50,303
Should he just give her a gift
all of a sudden?

116
00:08:08,988 --> 00:08:10,615
I already have a watch.

117
00:08:10,698 --> 00:08:13,659
It's Santa Claus who gives you
something you don't have.

118
00:08:15,036 --> 00:08:16,287
Did you not feel that way as a kid?

119
00:08:16,370 --> 00:08:17,747
How would Santa Clause know

120
00:08:17,830 --> 00:08:21,125
what I really need right now every time?

121
00:08:21,209 --> 00:08:22,376
I did.

122
00:08:22,627 --> 00:08:24,712
What I wanted a doll,

123
00:08:24,795 --> 00:08:27,298
but he would always give me new shoes

124
00:08:27,381 --> 00:08:31,093
or new clothes which I actually needed
at the moment.

125
00:08:31,969 --> 00:08:35,097
I thought to myself when I found out
my parents were actually Santa Claus.

126
00:08:35,181 --> 00:08:36,432
A gift should be

127
00:08:36,641 --> 00:08:40,269
something you don't actually need
but that makes you happy.

128
00:08:40,561 --> 00:08:43,481
But today isn't a special day.

129
00:08:43,564 --> 00:08:45,399
For me, it's the day
when I should give you a gift.

130
00:08:45,858 --> 00:08:48,319
What day is it?

131
00:08:48,402 --> 00:08:50,196
It's the day when I confess
my feelings for you.

132
00:08:52,323 --> 00:08:54,158
For the rest of my life...

133
00:08:55,201 --> 00:08:57,078
Gosh, just delete it.

134
00:08:57,537 --> 00:08:59,080
Should I make him look cool?

135
00:09:11,759 --> 00:09:13,010
Well...

136
00:09:13,886 --> 00:09:16,097
This is my workplace.

137
00:09:20,101 --> 00:09:21,185
Eat this first.

138
00:09:22,061 --> 00:09:24,313
Why are you talking to me like that?

139
00:09:24,897 --> 00:09:27,108
-Don't I look cool?
-You look like a fool.

140
00:09:27,191 --> 00:09:31,279
That fool loves you. The fool...

141
00:09:34,824 --> 00:09:37,076
Whatever, you fool.

142
00:09:49,463 --> 00:09:52,300
-Why are you back?
-I'm working outside. I'll get some rest.

143
00:09:53,217 --> 00:09:54,969
That doesn't sound like you.

144
00:09:56,971 --> 00:09:58,389
My gosh.

145
00:10:02,184 --> 00:10:06,105
Gosh, Ms. Lim.
I didn't know you were here.

146
00:10:08,858 --> 00:10:10,901
It's so nice to see you.

147
00:10:11,569 --> 00:10:13,487
I guess you were working.

148
00:10:13,821 --> 00:10:16,407
Well... Yes.

149
00:10:17,033 --> 00:10:20,328
Actually, I read your script.

150
00:10:20,411 --> 00:10:22,371
-How?
-You submitted it to a contest,

151
00:10:22,455 --> 00:10:25,124
so I got it from the broadcasting company.
I'm sorry.

152
00:10:25,207 --> 00:10:27,835
It's okay. I wrote it for people to read.

153
00:10:28,377 --> 00:10:29,879
Speaking of which,

154
00:10:30,963 --> 00:10:35,009
I heard you're still looking
for a production company.

155
00:10:35,635 --> 00:10:38,763
I hope I'm not interrupting your work.

156
00:10:38,846 --> 00:10:41,349
Of course you are. I'm being interrupted.

157
00:10:41,432 --> 00:10:42,933
I'll see you around then.

158
00:10:43,809 --> 00:10:45,936
My goodness. It's my bad.

159
00:10:46,395 --> 00:10:48,064
You look really worn out

160
00:10:48,147 --> 00:10:52,109
as you're so busy with your work.

161
00:10:52,610 --> 00:10:53,778
I shouldn't have bothered you.

162
00:10:54,862 --> 00:10:56,781
Make sure to take this regularly.

163
00:10:56,906 --> 00:10:59,033
Thank you. You can leave it there.

164
00:11:08,292 --> 00:11:10,127
Gosh, I'm disappointed.

165
00:11:10,753 --> 00:11:14,048
Hey, don't get disappointed
with something like this.

166
00:11:14,131 --> 00:11:17,134
I know what you mean,
but let me be disappointed all I want.

167
00:11:17,218 --> 00:11:19,053
Just stay lying down there
and get some rest.

168
00:11:25,518 --> 00:11:28,938
I hope to see you again
on a formal occasion next time.

169
00:11:29,021 --> 00:11:30,606
I'll pay you a visit.

170
00:11:31,107 --> 00:11:33,818
Thank you. I'll see you later.

171
00:11:47,915 --> 00:11:49,125
I'm hungry.

172
00:12:04,181 --> 00:12:06,392
Hello, Ms. Lim.

173
00:12:06,475 --> 00:12:08,352
I'm here to meet you.

174
00:12:09,437 --> 00:12:10,938
Hello.

175
00:12:12,648 --> 00:12:14,817
So this is how Hwang Han-ju ends up.

176
00:12:25,536 --> 00:12:28,372
I should have light breakfasts
from now on.

177
00:12:28,456 --> 00:12:32,042
Even when I have a heavy meal,
I become hungry anyway. Why is that?

178
00:12:33,252 --> 00:12:35,504
Whether you work your brains or your body,

179
00:12:35,588 --> 00:12:39,550
I heard the amount of labor that
contributes to your hunger is similar.

180
00:12:40,009 --> 00:12:41,927
I appreciate your hard work.

181
00:12:45,264 --> 00:12:46,348
Why?

182
00:12:46,807 --> 00:12:48,058
How much can you offer?

183
00:12:48,142 --> 00:12:51,020
Well... That's not what I can...

184
00:12:51,103 --> 00:12:53,522
You know how much
rookie writers usually get, right?

185
00:12:53,606 --> 00:12:54,523
Of course I do.

186
00:12:54,607 --> 00:12:56,525
But your case is different.

187
00:12:56,609 --> 00:12:58,486
We are well aware of that too.

188
00:12:58,569 --> 00:13:01,906
You worked on the project proposal
and wrote four episodes all by yourself.

189
00:13:01,989 --> 00:13:04,783
You even have a director to work on it.

190
00:13:05,701 --> 00:13:08,412
We will consider the initial cost
for planning and development,

191
00:13:08,496 --> 00:13:11,248
and it will be added to your pay.

192
00:13:11,332 --> 00:13:14,668
You can trust our company on that.

193
00:13:14,752 --> 00:13:16,504
Our CEO, Ms. Lee is
very precise about that part.

194
00:13:16,587 --> 00:13:19,298
I don't need you to be precise.
I hope to get more than that.

195
00:13:24,845 --> 00:13:28,307
Why should I get paid less
just because I'm a rookie writer?

196
00:13:28,390 --> 00:13:31,644
It's not like people wouldn't watch
my drama just because I'm new.

197
00:13:31,852 --> 00:13:33,562
I totally agree with you.

198
00:13:33,646 --> 00:13:36,273
That's why you should sign
a contract with our company.

199
00:13:36,357 --> 00:13:37,358
Why?

200
00:13:41,153 --> 00:13:42,154
Me?

201
00:13:43,697 --> 00:13:45,115
You just said that, didn't you?

202
00:13:46,325 --> 00:13:47,451
Yes.

203
00:13:48,953 --> 00:13:50,871
I'm just a salaried employee.

204
00:13:52,706 --> 00:13:55,584
I guess writers should take turns

205
00:13:55,668 --> 00:13:57,336
to become a producer.

206
00:13:57,419 --> 00:14:00,548
I just don't understand
the revenue system.

207
00:14:01,507 --> 00:14:04,468
A producer like me is
more quick and precise

208
00:14:04,552 --> 00:14:05,719
in the field.

209
00:14:05,803 --> 00:14:08,889
You might need emotions
when you finish your writing,

210
00:14:08,973 --> 00:14:12,434
but we need rationality to visualize it
at the film site.

211
00:14:18,774 --> 00:14:20,150
I can't believe this.

212
00:14:21,235 --> 00:14:23,445
-I just sounded very articulate, right?
-Yes.

213
00:14:23,529 --> 00:14:27,283
My gosh. I just can do it
when I'm cornered.

214
00:14:27,366 --> 00:14:31,203
I should've recorded it.
Do you remember what I just said?

215
00:14:31,287 --> 00:14:33,122
My goodness.

216
00:14:34,164 --> 00:14:36,375
You are really cute.

217
00:14:37,751 --> 00:14:39,503
I almost kissed you just now.

218
00:14:40,087 --> 00:14:42,756
How would you feel
if a guy asked you out saying that?

219
00:14:42,840 --> 00:14:45,509
"You are really cute.

220
00:14:45,593 --> 00:14:47,928
I almost kissed you just now."

221
00:14:49,305 --> 00:14:50,264
What?

222
00:14:50,347 --> 00:14:52,349
I'm writing a scene
where a guy asks a girl out.

223
00:14:53,100 --> 00:14:54,393
Yes, Ms. Lim.

224
00:14:57,187 --> 00:14:58,439
It sounds really weird.

225
00:14:58,522 --> 00:15:01,358
-The actor is Gang Dong-won.
-Then I'd ask him out first.

226
00:15:03,277 --> 00:15:05,321
I don't think
I can have him play this part.

227
00:15:06,196 --> 00:15:10,075
Jae-hun, what did you say
when you asked your girlfriend out?

228
00:15:13,037 --> 00:15:14,955
I just used an instant messenger.

229
00:15:16,248 --> 00:15:18,375
Gosh, should I make it
an instant messenger?

230
00:15:18,459 --> 00:15:20,544
It's a drama. It sounds too lame.

231
00:15:23,881 --> 00:15:26,050
It would sound new though.

232
00:15:26,467 --> 00:15:28,802
Has anyone asked you out recently?

233
00:15:29,595 --> 00:15:32,431
You know that better.
Who would ask me out?

234
00:15:32,514 --> 00:15:33,641
That's right.

235
00:15:34,642 --> 00:15:37,728
Oh, right. There was someone.

236
00:15:38,020 --> 00:15:39,855
Was it two years ago?

237
00:15:40,481 --> 00:15:43,192
Hey, it's not like he asked me out.

238
00:15:45,694 --> 00:15:47,613
Thank you for the dinner tonight.

239
00:15:50,616 --> 00:15:53,494
And thank you for walking me home.

240
00:15:54,995 --> 00:15:57,581
I'll treat you next time.

241
00:15:57,665 --> 00:15:58,791
Han-ju.

242
00:16:01,085 --> 00:16:04,672
I have a daughter who's in middle school.

243
00:16:06,048 --> 00:16:07,174
I have a family of two.

244
00:16:10,135 --> 00:16:11,929
And I want it to become a family of four.

245
00:16:17,768 --> 00:16:19,937
You want a family of four.

246
00:16:21,271 --> 00:16:23,774
You can laugh. It's okay.

247
00:16:25,275 --> 00:16:27,236
So what did you say?

248
00:16:27,778 --> 00:16:29,446
I did what Jin-joo told me to do.

249
00:16:30,739 --> 00:16:34,660
I gave him the number of a dog shelter
so he could adopt two dogs.

250
00:16:36,495 --> 00:16:39,206
-Did he?
-He got only one dog.

251
00:16:40,874 --> 00:16:44,670
So it became a family of three.
That's so funny.

252
00:16:45,462 --> 00:16:48,882
Tell me about your story.
It's unfair that I only shared mine.

253
00:16:52,219 --> 00:16:55,097
Actually, before I asked her out
using an instant messenger,

254
00:16:55,389 --> 00:16:57,099
-I got caught.
-What?

255
00:16:58,058 --> 00:16:58,934
All right.

256
00:16:59,018 --> 00:17:00,602
-Jae-hun's favorite
-Jae-hun's favorite

257
00:17:00,686 --> 00:17:01,937
-random game!
-random game!

258
