You're the boss. How can you say that?

342
00:22:58,794 --> 00:23:00,378
Just go to Haenaem ENT.

343
00:23:00,921 --> 00:23:03,965
We shot this by mistake
without their consent, right?

344
00:23:04,883 --> 00:23:05,884
Yes.

345
00:23:06,551 --> 00:23:08,720
-Go and delete it.
-What?

346
00:23:08,804 --> 00:23:11,473
It was shot without their consent.
We're not supposed to watch it.

347
00:23:11,681 --> 00:23:12,933
Be honest.

348
00:23:13,892 --> 00:23:14,935
Okay.

349
00:23:15,477 --> 00:23:19,356
You know what I mean.

350
00:23:19,481 --> 00:23:21,608
This is what I think you should do.

351
00:23:22,025 --> 00:23:24,194
In this situation...

352
00:23:24,277 --> 00:23:26,905
What are you doing?
I told you to delete it.

353
00:23:30,575 --> 00:23:32,327
COLD BEVERAGE

354
00:23:43,380 --> 00:23:44,840
I know it's just a vending machine.

355
00:23:44,923 --> 00:23:46,925
But 1,200 won for a bottle of water?

356
00:23:48,385 --> 00:23:49,553
You know the bakery around here

357
00:23:49,636 --> 00:23:51,179
increased the prices of their products?

358
00:23:51,763 --> 00:23:54,766
A sandwich that used to cost 5,000 won
came clean with me today.

359
00:23:55,183 --> 00:23:57,602
"Actually I'm worth 6,000 won."

360
00:24:00,397 --> 00:24:02,149
I don't have
enough production cost for this.

361
00:24:02,232 --> 00:24:03,650
This is quite nice.

362
00:24:04,734 --> 00:24:05,777
What?

363
00:24:05,861 --> 00:24:08,488
When we first met,
you were working on your project.

364
00:24:09,030 --> 00:24:10,532
This reminds me of the time.

365
00:24:11,783 --> 00:24:13,493
I know.

366
00:24:15,245 --> 00:24:19,291
But I feel like I'm not as strong
as I was back then

367
00:24:20,125 --> 00:24:21,960
when it comes to the shortage of money.

368
00:24:22,043 --> 00:24:23,879
You mean your physical strength?

369
00:24:24,212 --> 00:24:25,213
Yes.

370
00:24:25,714 --> 00:24:26,590
You took a long break,

371
00:24:26,673 --> 00:24:28,425
so it's taking you a long time
to get warmed up.

372
00:24:28,508 --> 00:24:29,342
Don't worry.

373
00:24:32,345 --> 00:24:35,307
Actually I invested the money
I made from the previous project

374
00:24:35,390 --> 00:24:37,350
in the project I'm working on now.

375
00:24:37,434 --> 00:24:40,020
I must say it's a reasonable investment.

376
00:24:40,187 --> 00:24:42,355
But the amount of money is so small.

377
00:24:43,315 --> 00:24:46,568
Do you think I gave
too much money to the charity?

378
00:24:47,360 --> 00:24:48,403
What?

379
00:24:49,404 --> 00:24:51,823
-What is that? Are you regretting it?
-What?

380
00:24:53,575 --> 00:24:55,076
No.

381
00:24:57,662 --> 00:25:00,207
Gosh, it's not like that.

382
00:25:02,584 --> 00:25:05,295
-Hello.
-Hi, So-min. Did you have a good rest?

383
00:25:05,378 --> 00:25:07,005
-Yes.
-Good.

384
00:25:08,924 --> 00:25:10,425
"Have a good rest?"

385
00:25:11,384 --> 00:25:13,220
Was he making fun of me
because I'm not busy enough?

386
00:25:13,553 --> 00:25:15,805
Gosh, it was nothing like that.

387
00:25:16,056 --> 00:25:17,057
Really?

388
00:25:17,474 --> 00:25:18,808
Does he like me then?

389
00:25:18,892 --> 00:25:20,560
My goodness.

390
00:25:21,269 --> 00:25:22,562
I'm sure he doesn't.

391
00:25:22,854 --> 00:25:24,147
Are you serious?

392
00:25:24,231 --> 00:25:26,399
I swear it was nothing like that.

393
00:25:26,483 --> 00:25:29,277
-Really?
-Yes.

394
00:25:30,153 --> 00:25:32,113
You can't be too sure about things.

395
00:25:32,447 --> 00:25:34,157
But this is so obvious.

396
00:25:40,497 --> 00:25:42,374
I know it can't be helped.

397
00:25:42,457 --> 00:25:44,000
But what about the money?

398
00:25:44,084 --> 00:25:45,794
Why is she talking to herself?

399
00:25:45,877 --> 00:25:47,921
I've seen her
talking to herself a few times.

400
00:25:48,338 --> 00:25:49,464
Why would she do that?

401
00:25:50,507 --> 00:25:51,633
Is she talking on the phone?

402
00:25:53,260 --> 00:25:54,636
Do you have any good ideas?

403
00:25:56,930 --> 00:25:58,890
THINGS WILL BE FINE ONCE YOU TURN THIRTY

404
00:26:02,519 --> 00:26:05,230
An RC car? I didn't know
you had a hobby like that.

405
00:26:05,313 --> 00:26:06,439
It's fun.

406
00:26:06,815 --> 00:26:09,567
I can connect it to a wagon
and give my kids a ride.

407
00:26:10,485 --> 00:26:13,154
Things Will Be Fine Once You Turn Thirty?

408
00:26:13,571 --> 00:26:14,906
Isn't the title a little weird?

409
00:26:14,990 --> 00:26:16,658
I picked it because I liked the title.

410
00:26:16,741 --> 00:26:19,953
"Things will get better
once you grow older."

411
00:26:20,412 --> 00:26:21,454
It's somewhat depressing.

412
00:26:21,538 --> 00:26:23,456
I think it's encouraging and comforting.

413
00:26:24,207 --> 00:26:25,875
Fine. Whatever.

414
00:26:26,543 --> 00:26:28,545
Young people seem to like it.

415
00:26:29,087 --> 00:26:30,922
I guess it will be
an unprecedented project.

416
00:26:31,256 --> 00:26:33,591
It will be aired
because of the regular employees,

417
00:26:33,675 --> 00:26:34,968
not the executives.

418
00:26:35,051 --> 00:26:36,636
It's about time to reform things.

419
00:26:38,638 --> 00:26:40,056
You know what?

420
00:26:40,598 --> 00:26:43,977
I had a drink with Hwan-dong and Dong-gi
a few days ago.

421
00:26:44,060 --> 00:26:45,603
I see.

422
00:26:47,022 --> 00:26:47,897
I'm not jealous.

423
00:26:47,981 --> 00:26:50,692
And Ms. Jung Hye-jeong was there.

424
00:26:51,443 --> 00:26:52,444
I'm sorry to hear that.

425
00:26:52,527 --> 00:26:54,487
And Ms. Jung asked Hwan-dong

426
00:26:54,571 --> 00:26:56,614
to direct her drama there.

427
00:26:58,908 --> 00:27:01,244
Oh, right. He used to work on her dramas.

428
00:27:01,328 --> 00:27:04,497
And Hwan-dong rejected it right away.

429
00:27:04,664 --> 00:27:05,749
He did.

430
00:27:06,207 --> 00:27:08,001
I taught him well.
That's what he should do.

431
00:27:08,084 --> 00:27:11,129
He just thought Ms. Jung was joking.

432
00:27:11,212 --> 00:27:13,131
If it was a joke, that's just mean.

433
00:27:13,590 --> 00:27:16,384
I'm not sure
if she's trying not to be mean.

434
00:27:17,260 --> 00:27:18,428
But the next day,

435
00:27:19,137 --> 00:27:21,556
he got an official offer
from the production company.

436
00:27:21,639 --> 00:27:25,393
I knew it. She's so good
at ruining people's relationships.

437
00:27:25,477 --> 00:27:26,811
And...

438
00:27:27,020 --> 00:27:30,315
do you know what Hwan-dong said

439
00:27:31,024 --> 00:27:32,317
to the official offer?

440
00:27:33,485 --> 00:27:37,364
Since he didn't consult me,
I bet he rejected it.

441
00:27:37,989 --> 00:27:38,990
Right.

442
00:27:46,831 --> 00:27:49,250
Mr. Son. Did you eat?

443
00:27:49,334 --> 00:27:51,336
Hey, Hwan-dong. Let's eat.

444
00:27:51,419 --> 00:27:53,671
The weather is... Gosh, what's that?

445
00:27:53,755 --> 00:27:56,299
Nothing. I'm just dumbfounded.

446
00:27:57,342 --> 00:27:58,968
Did you review Ms. Jung's script?

447
00:28:01,054 --> 00:28:03,932
How dare you review it?
You should've said yes right away.

448
00:28:04,808 --> 00:28:06,351
I will just make this short.

449
00:28:06,976 --> 00:28:08,728
You haven't given
the company your feedback yet.

450
00:28:08,812 --> 00:28:10,688
Just read the script first.

451
00:28:10,772 --> 00:28:11,981
Just do it if you like it by half.

452
00:28:12,065 --> 00:28:14,442
I mean, just do it
even if you don't like it.

453
00:28:14,734 --> 00:28:16,945
-Even if I don't like it?
-Hey.

454
00:28:17,362 --> 00:28:19,572
Making a debut with something you like?

455
00:28:20,073 --> 00:28:22,659
It's not going to happen
unless you write your own script.

456
00:28:22,742 --> 00:28:25,203
Making a debut with the script
of a writer who guarantees good ratings?

457
00:28:25,286 --> 00:28:27,789
It never happens
unless the writer is crazy.

458
00:28:27,872 --> 00:28:29,165
And the writer is crazy.

459
00:28:29,249 --> 00:28:31,000
Something impossible is happening.

460
00:28:31,084 --> 00:28:32,460
Just take the offer and do it.

461
00:28:32,919 --> 00:28:34,254
And show them what you can do.

462
00:28:34,337 --> 00:28:37,507
Then you'll be offered more choices.

463
00:28:38,091 --> 00:28:40,009
That's how you start things, okay?

464
00:28:40,093 --> 00:28:41,761
But my duty as an assistant director--

465
00:28:41,845 --> 00:28:45,181
You're not here as my assistant,
but as a director of JBC.

466
00:28:45,807 --> 00:28:47,976
You can't blow your own chances like that.

467
00:28:48,393 --> 00:28:49,769
That's just a dereliction of duty.

468
00:28:52,397 --> 00:28:55,442
Please stop being so naive, okay?

469
00:28:55,650 --> 00:28:58,278
You will only end up becoming a pushover.

470
00:29:00,530 --> 00:29:01,823
I'll review it.

471
00:29:03,032 --> 00:29:04,701
No, just accept it.

472
00:29:05,910 --> 00:29:07,245
Eat alone, you brat.

473
00:29:09,205 --> 00:29:10,331
Hello, Ms. Lim.

474
00:29:11,249 --> 00:29:12,959
I like you, Mr. Son.

475
00:29:15,420 --> 00:29:17,380
I said I like you.

476
00:29:18,339 --> 00:29:19,424
You must be depressed.

477
00:29:21,050 --> 00:29:24,429
Yes. I've been staying still,

478
00:29:24,763 --> 00:29:28,266
but now I want to move a little.

479
00:29:28,349 --> 00:29:31,478
-Get up then.
-No, I should stay still.

480
00:29:31,561 --> 00:29:33,688
I want the sofa to move.

481
00:29:35,815 --> 00:29:38,026
Do you want a flying carpet or something?

482
00:29:38,109 --> 00:29:39,444
Exactly.

483
00:29:39,986 --> 00:29:42,197
You're so smart.

484
00:29:44,699 --> 00:29:46,534
I can't get you a carpet.

485
00:30:07,847 --> 00:30:09,766
Asking someone out?

486
00:30:10,767 --> 00:30:11,851
You have to do it.

487
00:30:13,019 --> 00:30:14,771
I like something simple.

488
00:30:14,854 --> 00:30:16,356
A simple confession?

489
00:30:18,107 --> 00:30:20,235
My mom is quite simple.

490
00:30:20,443 --> 00:30:22,070
She asked my dad out first.

491
00:30:22,153 --> 00:30:24,030
Back in those days?

492
00:30:24,113 --> 00:30:27,617
She thought he was cool
to run his own business at a young age.

493
00:30:27,700 --> 00:30:29,410
-His own business?
-The laundry.

494
00:30:29,494 --> 00:30:31,246
That's not common.

495
00:30:31,621 --> 00:30:33,623
A young owner of the laundry.

496
00:30:52,308 --> 00:30:55,228
Mom was the daughter of the Chinese
restaurant across the street.

497
00:31:05,613 --> 00:31:07,031
I didn't order tangsuyuk.

498
00:31:08,741 --> 00:31:10,743
My daughter says she likes you.

499
00:31:29,095 --> 00:31:31,890
She asked her dad to say it.

500
00:31:32,390 --> 00:31:35,643
It's not simple. It's rather unique.

501
00:31:39,856 --> 00:31:41,232
-Just cut it.
-Okay.

502
00:31:44,736 --> 00:31:46,029
Eat some more.

503
00:31:46,946 --> 00:31:47,947
Just eat it.

504
00:31:55,121 --> 00:31:56,164
-It's good, isn't it?
-Yes.

505
00:31:56,873 --> 00:31:58,875
-Here.
-Put it here.

506
00:32:00,793 --> 00:32:02,545
What's the big deal
about a confession scene?

507
00:32:02,837 --> 00:32:04,130
It's not like you're doing it.

508
00:32:04,213 --> 00:32:06,966
I'm doing it. I'm writing the scene.

509
00:32:07,050 --> 00:32:10,511
You should use your skills as a writer.

510
00:32:12,096 --> 00:32:15,850
I wish it was
about some wrestling technique.

511
00:32:15,934 --> 00:32:18,519
That way I can be trained.
It would've been easier.

512
00:32:18,603 --> 00:32:20,647
This is either one of the two cases.

513
00:32:21,147 --> 00:32:22,231
What?

514
00:32:22,815 --> 00:32:24,317
First, you're so into the drama

515
00:32:24,400 --> 00:32:26,861
that you believe you're
the protagonist of the story.

516
00:32:26,945 --> 00:32:28,029
You mean I'm crazy.

517
00:32:28,112 --> 00:32:30,698
Second, this is about the fairness
of the story.

518
